    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Introduction: Why Shoes Matter</h2>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">
      Before we climb the ladder from 10 to 1, let us agree on something: shoes are not merely things we put on our feet. Shoes are civilization's silent narrators. They tell us who had power and who didn't, who could afford silk and who wrapped rawhide, who danced in Versailles and who worked sixteen-hour shifts in Lynn, Massachusetts. The story of shoes is the story of us — our wars, our loves, our industries, our rebellions, our insatiable desire to walk a little taller.
    </p>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">
      The ten people on this list didn't just make footwear. They bent history. Some with machines. Some with red nail polish and a wild idea. Some with waffle irons. Every single one left a footprint deeper than any sole could make.
    </p>

